Bring a #large saucepan{} of @water{} to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium high heat.

While the oil is heating up, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Add the pepper to the hot oil and fry until tender and coloured, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}), finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and all), thinly slice the @red chilli{½}(thinly sliced).

== Pasta ==

Add the @fresh tagliatelle{200%g} to the boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}, pop back in the pan, drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, once the pepper is soft, add the garlic and @peri peri seasoning{1%packet} and stir together. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}(350g jar), @water{100%ml} and add the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}.

Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}.

Add the @cooked pulled chicken{200%g}, stir together, bring to the boil and simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly and the chicken is piping hot, ~{2-3%mins}.

== To Serve ==

Taste the sauce and add salt, pepper and sugar if you feel it needs it.

Add the drained pasta to the sauce and toss together.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the sauce has reduced too much.

Serve the pasta in #bowls{} and grate over the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Sprinkle over the parsley and sliced chilli.

Serve with a handful of @wild rocket{40%g} on top and enjoy!